<dl id="n54148f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54148f">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54148f"> 148(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> oracle, <font color="green">[orders]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Lorsqu&apos;un Zande dit que le poison-<mark>oracle</mark> (celui qui sert &agrave; la divination) a un <i>mbisimo</i>, il ne veut gu&egrave;re faire entendre que ceci: &laquo;Il fait quelque chose, ou, comme nous dirions, <mark>il poss&egrave;de une force</mark>.&raquo; (Il est dynamique.) Demandez-leur alors comment ils savent que le poison a une &laquo;&acirc;me&raquo;, ils r&eacute;pondront qu&apos;ils le savent parce qu&apos;il agit. Ils expliquent l&apos;action mystique en lui donnant un nom. <br><font color="green">[When a Zande says that the poison-oracle (that which is used for divination) has a <i>mbisimo</i>, he does not want to make hear that this:" He does something thing, or, as we would say, it has a force. (He is dynamic.) Then ask them how they know the poison has a "soul", they will answer that they know it because it acts. They explain the mystical action by giving it a name."]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 291</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
